uote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222593308\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463780612\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat looks like an interesting mod.\u00A0 For your planned features, the body occlusion/graininess, you should consider integrating that with ScanSat\u0027s topographical scans if you can.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the plan. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E Waiting for \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57416-dmagic/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257416\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57416-dmagic/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DMagic\u003C/a\u003E to get back to me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-20T21:47:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222593313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463780725\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the plan. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E Waiting for \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57416-dmagic/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257416\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57416-dmagic/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DMagic\u003C/a\u003E to get back to me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool, I love ScanSat, but one of the things I hate about it is it\u0027s maps, I\u0027ve always wished it could somehow overlay them in the KSP map instead of a separate window.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DMagic","CreatedById":57416,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-21T01:30:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110959\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Alshain\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Do you mean overlaying the map onto the planet in map view? Like This:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/vks7Y/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-21T01:31:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222593636\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463794245\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257416\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DMagic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, DMagic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110959\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Alshain\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Do you mean overlaying the map onto the planet in map view? Like This:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/vks7Y/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHoly crap, I didn\u0027t know it could do that!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-21T02:03:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry I misunderstood. My idea is to use ResearchBodies to progressively discover and reveal the details of each Celestial Body.\u003Cbr\u003E\nTo do this you would use TST telescopes, DMagic OS scanners and ScanSAT scanners to reveal the details of each Body.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57416-dmagic/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257416\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57416-dmagic/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DMagic\u003C/a\u003E mentioned \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/109207-11-orbital-survey-plus-21-overhaul-now-with-real-time-scanning-and-science/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=2564896\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E potentially some starting point /codebase for it. I\u0027m waiting for him to respond to a PM. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DMagic","CreatedById":57416,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-21T02:21:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u00A0Code\u0027s a mess; I\u0027ll get to it eventually though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-21T02:28:26Z\u0022 title=\u002205/21/2016 02:28  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 21, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DMagic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"THX1138","CreatedById":113955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-13T16:25:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like the idea. I think it would also be cool to discover a moon or planet that you weren\u0027t aware of/wasn\u0027t in the tracking station at the beginning of the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-13T18:44:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/139473-112-researchbodies-v172-1st-june-2016/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;embedComment=2626436\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}